Excellent Lamb Recipe

Rating: 3
Perfect and easy! Since I didn't have savory in my garden, I used just the thyme and rosemary and added 3 extra garlic cloves. Looking over the reviews, I decided to cook at high temp (425) for the first 20 minutes minus the same amount of time in the recipe. I didn't cook the potatoes before hand due to the comment of them being overcooked. I placed them and the onions with the beef stock salt and pepper in the roasting pan and placed the lamb on top and started from there. After removing the roast and left to rest I changed the oven to broil and slightly browned the potatoes tossing until they were all golden. My roast was 6 3/4 pounds and cooked perfectly, medium rare, rare and a few well done pieces so everyone was happy!

