Rating: 3
We loved this!! It was flavorful and the lamb remained tender. The onions and the potatoes were a great accompaniment to the lamb and utterly delicious!!

Rating: 3
This was so easy! I skipped the savory (couldnt find it) and used golden delicious potatoes intsead of russet. Go with the fresh herbs and mince them in a grinder. Half an hour into it I squeezed half a lemon over the lamb 'cuz that sounded good in other recipes. Half an hour after that I basted the potatoes with a little reserved beef broth to deglaze the pan and add a little moisture to them then basted the lamb with the pan juices after that. I used a meat thermometer rather than depend on the time and cooked it to 145 and let it stand for about 30 minutes before we were ready to eat. Everyone loved it (some real picky eaters here), it tasted great (and I love lamb), and I can't wait to try it again! This was the easiest thing I've ever made for a special dinner like this! A real keeper.

