Rating: 4
If you love lamb, this is the dish for you. I decided to skip the step of putting the garlic slices into the lamb. Instead, I put whole cloves of garlic into the roasting pan with the potatoes. It came out great.

Rating: 3
Easy and simple to make and tastes great. And the best thing of all low fat. I did not find it necessary to baste the meat. The evaporating juices in the pan make the oven fairly humid and thus no basting. That is, if your oven is good.

Rating: 3
After checking out a few of the leg of lamb recipes on the site I decided to go with this one and I'm glad I did. It was my first try with a leg of lamb and it was delicious. I used a smaller New Zealand spring lamb, adjusting my time accordingly, and the lamb was cooked to perfection. I should have started the potatoes earlier because even after turning up the heat again and leaving them in the oven while the lamb rested they still didn't get the crust that I was looking for. Despite this, it was still a wonderful meal (served with watercress & spinach and yellow beans) and my 14 month old gobbled up the leftovers for lunch and dinner the next day. Thanks for the tip about the basting. I used beer and I'm sure that helped to prevent the meat from drying out.

Rating: 4
This recipe was absolutely perfect. All of their flavors complemented eachother so incredibly well. I kept checking the lamb to make sure it wasn't drying out and I added a beer throughtout the cooking time to baste it. I also used a boneless lamb and cooked it for about 1 hour 10 minutes for medium rare. All of my guests loved it. Its a keeper and I will make this again and again.

Rating: 2
Although the tastes were good in this recipe, the lamb came out too dry. The recipe states to cook the lamb for 1 hour and 50 minutes for medium rare. That may have been too long as the meat came out dry and tough. Maybe covering the meat would have helped, or basting or searing. I don't know. Is it worth trying again? I don't think it is worth it because a leg of lamb is not exactly inexpensive. Lamb is not supposed to be so dry. I agree that the potatoes were good but try another lamb recipe.

